text: Just came back from a screening. Great, awesome horror movie with an interesting good plot. I like how the main girl receives this creepy chinese music box and she can have 7 wishes. But everytime she makes a wish, someone will die. There is also another twist which I shall not reveal. The death scenes are creative, like those from the "Final Destination" movies. My favourite has got to be the elevator death scene because it's so intense and scary. You have no idea who is going to die next. It's either the father or one of the best friends because the editing plays around you and put you at the edge of your seat. I mean, you have to see it for yourself. The way the elevator came crashing down, it's so frightening.  Another death scene that involves hair getting stuck in the sink razor with no chance of escaping is pretty good too. I like how the movie explores the backstory of the music box. Anyway, the main girl thought she outsmarts the music box but it didn't turn out that way at all.....When the movie concludes, you will feel sad and sorry for the main girl..... Great, amazing horror movie.
